    <h3>Contents</h3>
<ol>
  <li><a href="#field-collection-2">Field Collection</a></li>
  <li><a href="#equipment-2">Equipment</a></li>
  <li>
    <a href="#instructions-and-procedures-2">Instructions and procedures</a>
  </li>
  <li><a href="#additional-guidelines-2">Additional guidelines</a></li>
<li><a href="#references">References</a></li>
</ol>
<h1 id="soil-sample-pit">Soil Sample Pit</h1>
<h2 id="field-collection-2">Field collection</h2>
<h3 id="pre-requisites-2">Pre-requisites</h3>
<p>Pre-requisites for completing this protocol:</p>
<ul>
<li><p>Before commencing the survey, the <a href="https://linked.data.gov.au/def/nrm/d15d05db-5007-411e-b257-105ef4f76821">Plot Selection and Layout Module</a> must be completed.</p></li>
<li><p>The <a href="https://linked.data.gov.au/def/nrm/1ff9e97c-3bdd-44c9-bdd3-401fa31c0b32">Plot Description Module</a> must be completed before, during or
after the protocol. The <a href="https://linked.data.gov.au/def/nrm/1ff9e97c-3bdd-44c9-bdd3-401fa31c0b32">Plot Description Module</a> is best completed by
personnel familiar with describing the landforms and vegetation
communities.</p></li>
<li><p>The protocol involves the collection and transportation of soil
samples, requiring appropriate scientific permits and approvals.
Movement of soil samples may involve obtaining a biosecurity permit,
which can entail safe packaging, proper labelling, and documentation.
Check with the local authority for specific requirements.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id="time-requirements-2">Time requirements</h3>
<p>Survey time requirements will vary depending on the number and
experience of the personnel, the soil type and depth. As a general
guide:</p>
<ul>
<li><p>Allow between 2 - 3 hours for digging of the soil pit.</p></li>
<li><p>Allow between 1 - 2 hours to collect soil samples and record the
information.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id="personnel-requirements-2">Personnel requirements</h3>
<p>Number of personnel and skills:</p>
<ul>
<li><p>Completing the <em>Soil sample pit protocol</em> is best
conducted with two personnel, to assist with digging of the soil pit.
Once the soil pit has been completed, one surveyor can sample the pit
and the other records the data directly into the app.  </p></li>
<li><p>The surveyors should be familiar with excavating a soil pit, soil
characteristics and procedures for collecting soil samples. If surveyors
are not confident, time should be dedicated to practising, using
instruction manuals, and seeking advice before conducting this
protocol. </p></li>
</ul>
<br> <p><img id="figure-1" alt="Figure-1" height="600" src="https://w3id.org/tern/static/dawe-rlp/latest/soil/Fig1_plot_layout.png" width="1000"/></p>
Figure 1. Core plot with indicative locations of the soil pit and nine soil sub-pits across the plot.<br>
